@startuml UpdateOrderStatus
title Update Order Status Flow with Event Publishing

actor "Kitchen\nStaff" as Staff
participant "API\nGateway" as Gateway
participant "Order Status\nService" as OSS
participant "ActiveMQ\nBroker" as Queue
participant "Notification\nService" as NS
participant "Order\nService" as OS
database "Status DB" as DB

Staff -> Gateway: POST /orders/{orderId}/status\n{status: "PREPARING", updatedBy: "chef"}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> OSS: Forward request
activate OSS

OSS -> DB: RECORD StatusHistory\nstatus=PREPARING, timestamp=now
activate DB
DB --> OSS: OrderStatusHistory{id, status, timestamp}
deactivate DB

OSS -> Queue: PUBLISH Event\nOrderStatusChangedEvent
activate Queue

note over OSS
  Event Details:
  - orderId, newStatus
  - oldStatus, timestamp
  - updatedBy: "chef"
  - eventId: UUID (idempotent)
end note

Queue -> NS: Topic: order-status-changed
activate NS
Queue -> OS: Async listener receives event
activate OS

NS --> Queue: Event processed
deactivate NS

OS -> OS: UPDATE Order.status=PREPARING
deactivate OS
deactivate Queue

OSS --> Gateway: HTTP 201 Created
deactivate OSS
Gateway --> Staff: StatusHistory response
deactivate Gateway
@enduml
